This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of 3D cardiac MR images. The use of convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of auxiliary side paths to strengthen gradient propagation, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks for optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
